<title>USA: Carson buys product line from USA Co.</title>
<headline>Carson buys product line from USA Co.</headline>
<dateline>SAVANNAH, Ga 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Carson Inc said Tuesday it signed an agreement with Chesebrough-Pond's USA Co to acquire the full CUTEX product line and trademarks for exclusive use in the United States and Puerto Rico.</p>
<p>Pending regulatory approval, the transaction, worth more than $30 million, is expected to be completed by April 30.</p>
<p>The company said the purchase included the CUTEX Nail Polish Remover, as well as Cutex nail care and lip color products, previously licensed to Jean Philippe Fragrances Inc.</p>
<p>In 1996, the total CUTEX product line generated approximately $27.5 million in net revenues, it said.</p>
<p>Carson makes hair care products for people of African descent.</p>
